msgstr "最后，要特别感谢 Sanne Grinovero，感谢他适时地将我们介绍给莱登团队，并对我们的工作提出了真知灼见和宝贵意见。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "What is Project Leyden?"
msgstr "什么是莱顿项目？"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "GraalVM and the popularization of AOT in Java"
msgstr "GraalVM 和 Java 中 AOT 的普及"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"In the Java world, Ahead-of-Time (AOT) compilation rose to prominence with "
"the introduction of GraalVM native image, which compiles Java applications "
"into native executables."
msgstr ""
"在 Java 领域，随着将 Java 应用程序编译成本地可执行文件的 GraalVM 本地映像的推出，Ahead-of-"
"Time（AOT）编译技术崭露头角。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"It made a huge impact on the Java ecosystem and was a game changer for Java "
"application startup performance:"
msgstr "它对 Java 生态系统产生了巨大影响，改变了 Java 应用程序启动性能的游戏规则："

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Startup time and memory footprint are significantly reduced."
msgstr "启动时间和内存占用大大减少。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"There is no warmup phase, as the code is already compiled to native code. "
"Performance is effectively at its peak from the start."
msgstr "由于代码已编译为本地代码，因此不存在热身阶段。性能从一开始就能有效地达到峰值。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The resulting executable is small, leading to much smaller container images."
msgstr "生成的可执行文件很小，因此容器映像也小得多。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The Resident Set Size (RSS) memory usage is much smaller compared to a "
"regular JVM application."
msgstr "与普通 JVM 应用程序相比，驻留集大小 (RSS) 内存用量要小得多。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "But this comes with some drawbacks:"
msgstr "但这也有一些缺点："

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Not all Java features and libraries are supported out of the box as they are "
"on OpenJDK."
msgstr "并非所有 Java 功能和库都能像 OpenJDK 一样获得开箱即用的支持。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"It relies on a closed-world assumption and removes most runtime dynamism (at "
"least in its current form - work on the GraalVM side could change this in "
"the future). Note: This was not and is not an issue for Quarkus as it makes "
"the same assumption; it can be problematic for third-party libraries."
msgstr ""
"它依赖于一个封闭世界的假设，并消除了大部分运行时的动态性（至少在当前形式下是这样--GraalVM "
"方面的工作可能会在未来改变这一点）。注：Quarkus 在过去和现在都不存在这个问题，因为它做出了同样的假设；但对于第三方库来说，这可能是个问题。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"It introduces specific constraints, the most common being the need to "
"provide explicit reflection configuration. These requirements add effort "
"during development and testing, although they are minimized for Quarkus "
"supported extensions."
msgstr ""
"它引入了特定的限制条件，最常见的是需要提供明确的反射配置。这些要求增加了开发和测试过程中的工作量，不过对于 Quarkus "
"支持的扩展来说，这些要求已经降到了最低。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Native image builds are significantly slower. This typically does not affect "
"the inner development loop (except when debugging native-specific issues), "
"but it can have a noticeable impact on CI resources."
msgstr "原生镜像的构建速度会明显变慢。这通常不会影响内部开发循环（调试本地特定问题时除外），但会对 CI 资源产生明显影响。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Debugging native executables is hard. It has improved, but it is still a lot "
"harder than debugging in the JVM as it requires the use of GDB and the "
"presence of debug symbols in the build."
msgstr "调试本地可执行文件很难。现在情况有所改善，但仍比在 JVM 中调试困难得多，因为它需要使用 GDB 并在构建过程中使用调试符号。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"And since everything is AOT-compiled, there is no JIT compiler to optimize "
"code at runtime, which can lead to suboptimal peak performance in some cases."
""
msgstr "由于所有代码都是 AOT 编译的，因此没有 JIT 编译器在运行时对代码进行优化，这在某些情况下会导致峰值性能不理想。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"All in all, native image is an excellent option when startup time and "
"footprint are the primary goals."
msgstr "总之，如果以启动时间和占用空间为主要目标，本机图像是一个很好的选择。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"However, not all applications optimize for those dimensions.\n"
"Some prioritize peak throughput, development velocity, debuggability, and "
"compatibility with existing tooling.\n"
"This is where Leyden becomes interesting, aiming to improve startup and "
"footprint while staying closer to the traditional JVM model."
msgstr ""
"然而，并非所有应用程序都针对这些方面进行优化。有些应用程序会优先考虑峰值吞吐量、开发速度、可调试性以及与现有工具的兼容性。这就是 Leyden "
"变得有趣的地方，它旨在改善启动和占用空间，同时更接近传统的 JVM 模型。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Project Leyden's approach to AOT"
msgstr "莱顿项目的 AOT 方法"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Project Leyden addresses the same fundamental problem as GraalVM native "
"image, but takes a different approach:"
msgstr "Project Leyden 解决了与 GraalVM 原生镜像相同的基本问题，但采用了不同的方法："

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"It is still \"pure\" Java, it is part of OpenJDK: your application runs on "
"the JVM, with full access to Java features and libraries, without special "
"configuration."
msgstr "它仍然是 \"纯 \"Java，是 OpenJDK 的一部分：您的应用程序在 JVM 上运行，可以完全访问 Java 功能和库，无需特殊配置。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"During a training phase, it records application behavior and gathers "
"information such as loaded and linked classes, and in more recent versions "
"also starts recording some JIT output - increasing scope and optimization "
"potentials in each JVM version."
msgstr ""
"在训练阶段，它记录应用程序的行为并收集信息，如加载和链接的类，在较新的版本中还开始记录一些 JIT 输出--在每个 JVM "
"版本中都增加了范围和优化潜力。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "This information is stored in an AOT cache file."
msgstr "这些信息存储在 AOT 缓存文件中。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "At startup, you configure the JVM with this AOT cache file."
msgstr "启动时，您将使用此 AOT 缓存文件配置 JVM。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Because the application still runs on the JVM, you continue to benefit from "
"the JIT compiler, your preferred garbage collector, and all other JVM "
"optimizations, preserving the high throughput typically associated with the "
"JVM."
msgstr ""
"由于应用程序仍在 JVM 上运行，因此您将继续受益于 JIT 编译器、首选垃圾回收器和所有其他 JVM 优化功能，并保持通常与 JVM 相关的高吞吐量。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The AOT cache is exactly that: a cache. If a class is not present in the "
"cache, it is loaded and linked as usual."
msgstr "AOT 缓存就是缓存。如果缓存中没有某个类，则会像往常一样加载和链接该类。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Project Leyden reduces startup time by optimizing class loading and linking.\n"
"It reduces warmup time by providing the JVM with profiling information, and "
"will reduce it even further once compiled code itself is stored in the cache."
""
msgstr ""
"Project Leyden 通过优化类加载和链接缩短了启动时间。它通过向 JVM "
"提供剖析信息来缩短预热时间，一旦编译代码本身存储在缓存中，预热时间将进一步缩短。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "How Leyden works"
msgstr "莱顿如何运作"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "That said, Project Leyden is not magic either. In its current form:"
msgstr "尽管如此，\"莱登计划 \"也并非神奇。就目前的形式而言"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Startup and warmup time improvements are significant, but not as substantial "
"as with GraalVM/Mandrel native image."
msgstr "启动和预热时间有明显改善，但不如 GraalVM/Mandrel 本机镜像那样显著。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You must train your application and generate the AOT cache. In practice, "
"this is not difficult, and in Quarkus, we have made it as seamless as "
"possible."
msgstr "您必须训练您的应用程序并生成 AOT 缓存。实际上，这并不难，在 Quarkus 中，我们尽可能做到了无缝衔接。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "You still need to ship a JVM with your application."
msgstr "您仍然需要将 JVM 与应用程序一起发送。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You also need to ship the AOT cache, which means container images will be "
"significantly larger than with native executables."
msgstr "您还需要运行 AOT 缓存，这意味着容器映像将比本地可执行文件大得多。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You don't get any memory footprint benefit yet: in most cases, it's "
"comparable to a regular JVM."
msgstr "你还不会获得任何内存占用的好处：在大多数情况下，它与普通的 JVM 不相上下。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Our take is that Project Leyden offers a compelling balance between "
"performance and compatibility, at a very reasonable cost,\n"
"and could become part of the default deployment workflow for many Java "
"applications running on the JVM."
msgstr ""
"我们认为，Project Leyden 以非常合理的成本在性能和兼容性之间实现了令人信服的平衡，可以成为许多在 JVM 上运行的 Java "
"应用程序的默认部署工作流程的一部分。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Project Leyden status"
msgstr "莱顿项目现状"

