#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Project Leyden in Quarkus"
msgstr "夸克斯的莱登项目"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Quarkus is a highly specialized framework, with extensive build-time "
"processing and optimizations.\n"
"Project Leyden is a specialized technology as well, with its own constraints "
"and requirements."
msgstr "Quarkus 是一个高度专业化的框架，具有广泛的构建时处理和优化功能。莱登项目也是一种专业技术，有自己的限制和要求。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Our goal was to integrate Project Leyden into Quarkus in a way that "
"preserves what Quarkus does best, while also maximizing the benefits of "
"Leyden."
msgstr ""
"我们的目标是将 Project Leyden 整合到 Quarkus 中，既保留 Quarkus 的优点，又最大限度地发挥 Leyden 的优势。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Quarkus 3.32 includes the first version of our end-to-end Leyden integration."
" Let's take a closer look at how it works."
msgstr "Quarkus 3.32 包含端到端莱登集成的第一个版本。让我们仔细看看它是如何工作的。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "AOT JAR packaging"
msgstr "AOT JAR 包装"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You may be used to seeing your Quarkus application packaged in a `target/"
"quarkus-app/` directory, but that wasn't always the case.\n"
"In the early days of Quarkus, we built a traditional runner JAR in `target/"
"`, with dependencies placed in a `lib/` directory, much like most other Java "
"frameworks."
msgstr ""
"你可能习惯于将 Quarkus 应用程序打包在 `target/quarkus-app/` 目录中，但并非总是如此。在 Quarkus 的早期，我们在 "
"`target/` 中构建了一个传统的运行程序 JAR，并将依赖项放在 `lib/` 目录中，这与大多数其他 Java 框架非常相似。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The current default packaging in Quarkus is called `fast-jar`.\n"
"One of its primary goals is to optimize class loading."
msgstr "Quarkus 当前的默认打包方式称为 `fast-jar` 。其主要目标之一是优化类加载。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"We achieved this by introducing our own class loader, which, for example, "
"keeps a `package name` -> `jar file` mapping in memory.\n"
"It also includes additional optimizations, such as maintaining a full "
"directory index for specific locations like `META-INF/services`.\n"
"These are just a few examples of what this packaging does, but they should "
"give you some context."
msgstr ""
"为此，我们引入了自己的类加载器，例如在内存中保留 `package name` → `jar file` 映射。它还包括额外的优化，例如为 `META-"
"INF/services` 等特定位置维护完整的目录索引。这些只是该打包功能的几个示例，但可以为您提供一些背景信息。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"This packaging performs very well in the traditional JVM world, but it "
"doesn't play nicely with Project Leyden."
msgstr "这种封装在传统的 JVM 世界中表现非常出色，但在 Project Leyden 中却不尽如人意。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Project Leyden takes a conservative approach: it only caches classes loaded "
"by the standard JDK class loaders.\n"
"In other words, no custom class loaders are allowed if you want to fully "
"benefit from AOT caching."
msgstr ""
"Project Leyden 采用了一种保守的方法：它只缓存由标准 JDK 类加载器加载的类。换句话说，如果想充分利用 AOT "
"缓存，就不能使用自定义类加载器。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"We hope that, at some point, this limitation will be lifted by the Leyden "
"team.\n"
"If that happens, we will return to the `fast-jar` packaging, or an evolution "
"of it."
msgstr "我们希望莱登团队能在某个时候取消这一限制。届时，我们将重新使用 `fast-jar` 包装，或对其进行改进。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"To be precise: you cannot use custom class loaders to load **classes** if "
"you want to fully benefit from AOT caching.\n"
"However, you can still use a custom class loader for loading **resources** "
"only."
msgstr "准确地说：如果想充分利用 AOT 缓存，就不能使用自定义类加载器加载 *类* 。不过，您仍然可以使用自定义类加载器来加载 *资源* 。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"This is why we developed a dedicated packaging for Project Leyden: `aot-jar`."
"\n"
"It is automatically selected when AOT is enabled, making the transition "
"completely transparent.\n"
"It uses the same file layout as the `fast-jar` packaging."
msgstr ""
"因此，我们为莱登项目开发了一个专用包装： `aot-jar` 。当启用 AOT 时，它将自动被选中，使过渡完全透明。它使用与 `fast-jar` "
"包装相同的文件布局。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"In addition to delegating all **class** loading to the JDK class loader, "
"this packaging has a few specific characteristics:"
msgstr "除了将所有 *类* 加载委托给 JDK 类加载器外，这种打包还有一些特殊的特点："

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"It collects service descriptors from `META-INF/services`, aggregates them, "
"and keeps them in memory."
msgstr "它从 `META-INF/services` 收集服务描述符，将其汇总并保存在内存中。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"It applies the same approach to Quarkus configuration files (e.g., "
"`application.properties`)."
msgstr "它对 Quarkus 配置文件（如 `application.properties` ）采用了同样的方法。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"It maintains a full index of specific directories (e.g., the root directory, "
"`META-INF`, and `META-INF/services`)."
msgstr "它维护特定目录（如根目录、 `META-INF` 和 `META-INF/services` ）的完整索引。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"It introduces a pre-initialization phase, during which selected elements are "
"preloaded in parallel (e.g., the time zone database)."
msgstr "它引入了一个预初始化阶段，在这一阶段，选定的元素会被并行预加载（例如时区数据库）。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"As this packaging format is new, we hope to gather feedback from real-world "
"usage."
msgstr "由于这种包装形式是全新的，我们希望从实际使用中收集反馈意见。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Let's be clear: `aot-jar` performs worse than `fast-jar` when Project Leyden "
"is not used."
msgstr "让我们明确一点：在不使用莱登项目的情况下， `aot-jar` 的性能比 `fast-jar` 差。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"It does not include all the optimizations of `fast-jar` and is intended to "
"be used only in conjunction with Project Leyden.\n"
"So it should not be used outside of this specific use case."
msgstr "它并不包括 `fast-jar` 的所有优化功能，而且只能与 Project Leyden 结合使用。因此，不应在此特定用例之外使用它。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Training and AOT cache generation"
msgstr "培训和 AOT 缓存生成"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The AOT cache is only as good as the training data used to generate it.\n"
"During the training phase, the JVM records which classes are loaded and "
"linked, and collects method profiling data.\n"
"The more representative the training workload, the more effective the "
"resulting cache."
