#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"In terms of RSS, Project Leyden does not significantly change the picture,\n"
"while native executables offer a substantially lower memory footprint."
msgstr "就 RSS 而言，Project Leyden 并没有明显改变，而本地可执行文件则大大减少了内存占用。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Reducing memory usage has not been a primary goal of Project Leyden so far,\n"
"though this may evolve in the future."
msgstr "到目前为止，减少内存使用量还不是莱登项目的主要目标，但未来可能会有所发展。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Let's take a step back"
msgstr "让我们后退一步"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"At this point, you might be thinking: \"Why not just go native for "
"everything?\".\n"
"For all the reasons <<graalvm,we've outlined>>, use native when it makes "
"sense for you."
msgstr "说到这里，你可能会想\"为什么不什么都用原生语言呢？基于 xref:graalvm[我们所概述的] 所有原因，在合理的情况下使用原生语言。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"There's also the question of throughput.\n"
"We haven't collected throughput numbers ourselves, as we didn't have the "
"proper setup,\n"
"but some of our colleagues are running tests in an isolated environment,\n"
"and recently published https://quarkus.io/blog/new-benchmarks/[new benchmark "
"results].\n"
"Native executables usually result in lower throughput,\n"
"at least with what is available as Open Source today in Mandrel and GraalVM "
"CE."
msgstr ""
"还有吞吐量的问题。我们自己没有收集吞吐量数据，因为我们没有适当的设置，但我们的一些同事正在隔离环境中运行测试，并在最近公布了 link:https://"
"quarkus.io/blog/new-benchmarks/[新的基准] 测试 link:https://quarkus.io/blog/new-"
"benchmarks/[结果] 。本地可执行文件通常会导致较低的吞吐量，至少 Mandrel 和 GraalVM CE 中的开源可执行文件是如此。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"This is where Project Leyden really shines: you get significantly faster "
"startup times compared to a regular JVM,\n"
"while still retaining all the benefits of running on the JVM."
msgstr "这正是 Project Leyden 真正的优势所在：与普通 JVM 相比，启动时间大大缩短，同时还保留了在 JVM 上运行的所有优势。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "What's next for Leyden in Quarkus?"
msgstr "莱登在夸克斯的下一步是什么？"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Project Leyden is actively evolving, and we are closely tracking its "
"developments,\n"
"in particular via the premain branch of the OpenJDK Leyden repository,\n"
"where experimental features are developed before being integrated into "
"mainline JDK releases."
msgstr "莱登项目正在积极发展，我们正在密切跟踪其发展情况，特别是通过 OpenJDK Leyden 存储库的预主分支。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "There are several areas where we expect things to improve:"
msgstr "我们期望在几个方面有所改进："

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Storage of JIT-compiled code in the AOT cache, which would further reduce "
"warmup time."
msgstr "在 AOT 缓存中存储 JIT 编译的代码，从而进一步缩短预热时间。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Potential support for custom class loaders, which would allow us to return "
"to the more optimized `fast-jar` packaging."
msgstr "对自定义类加载器的潜在支持，这将使我们能够回到更优化的 `fast-jar` 包装。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "On the Quarkus side, we are also working on:"
msgstr "在 Quarkus 方面，我们也在开展工作："

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Testing and validating on additional platforms, including Windows."
msgstr "在包括 Windows 在内的其他平台上进行测试和验证。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"As Project Leyden matures, we will continue to integrate new features into "
"Quarkus.\n"
"We are looking forward to what Java 27 and beyond will bring."
msgstr "随着莱登项目的成熟，我们将继续把新功能集成到 Quarkus 中。我们期待着 Java 27 及以后的发展。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
msgid "Conclusion"
msgstr "解决方案"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"After a month of experimenting and working on the integration of Project "
"Leyden into Quarkus, we are very excited about the results and the potential "
"of this technology.\n"
"And we are very happy we were able to integrate it into Quarkus 3.32 so that "
"you can play with it already."
msgstr ""
"经过一个月将莱登项目集成到 Quarkus 中的实验和工作，我们对这项技术的成果和潜力感到非常兴奋。我们很高兴能将其集成到 Quarkus 3.32 "
"中，这样您就可以使用它了。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Project Leyden is being continuously improved and is likely to figure "
"prominently in the future of the Java platform.\n"
"As part of our quest in Quarkus to provide the best development platform, "
"with the help of the OpenJDK team at IBM,\n"
"we are actively monitoring the progress made upstream (in the `premain` "
"branch of https://github.com/openjdk/leyden/tree/premain[`git@github.com:"
"openjdk/leyden.git`])\n"
"and plan to continue shaping the Quarkus + Leyden experience accordingly."
msgstr ""
"莱登项目正在不断改进，并有可能在 Java 平台的未来发展中占据重要地位。在 IBM OpenJDK 团队的帮助下，作为我们 Quarkus "
"致力于提供最佳开发平台的努力的一部分，我们正在积极监控上游（在 `premain` 分支中）取得的进展，并计划相应地继续塑造 Quarkus + "
"Leyden 体验。 link:https://github.com/openjdk/leyden/tree/premain[git@github."
"com:openjdk/leyden.git] 分支中）取得的进展，并计划据此继续塑造 Quarkus + Leyden 体验。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"With AOT support, Quarkus expands its runtime flexibility: plain JVM, Leyden-"
"optimized JVM, and native image."
msgstr "有了 AOT 支持，Quarkus 扩展了运行时的灵活性：纯 JVM、Leyden 优化 JVM 和本地映像。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Rather than replacing one another, these modes form a spectrum of trade-offs."
"\n"
"Native image remains unmatched for startup and minimal footprint.\n"
"Leyden strengthens the JVM startup story."
msgstr "这些模式并没有相互替代，而是形成了一个权衡范围。本地映像在启动和最小占用空间方面仍然无与伦比。Leyden 强化了 JVM 的启动。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Which works best depends on your priorities, constraints, and application "
"workload."
msgstr "哪种方法最有效取决于你的优先级、限制条件和应用工作量。"

#: _posts/2026-03-05-leyden-2.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Our commitment is unchanged: give developers the best option for their "
"workload and keep improving each path."
msgstr "我们的承诺始终如一：为开发人员的工作量提供最佳选择，并不断改进每一条路径。"

